66
00:08:11,675 --> 00:08:15,221
<i>Among the deceased was Adaline's husband.</i>

67
00:08:23,050 --> 00:08:28,576
<i>Ten months after her husband's death
Adaline was driving north to her</i>

68
00:08:28,665 --> 00:08:34,561
<i>parents beach cottage where 5 year
old Fleming was waiting up for her,</i>

69
00:08:35,932 --> 00:08:42,832
<i>when something highly unusual occurred,
something almost magical...</i>

70
00:08:47,629 --> 00:08:51,683
<i>snow fell in Sonoma County, California.</i>

71
00:09:26,368 --> 00:09:32,147
<i>The immersion in the frigid water
caused Adaline's body to go into an</i>

72
00:09:32,235 --> 00:09:40,033
<i>anoxic reflex, instantly stopping her
breathing and slowing her heartbeat.</i>

73
00:09:41,395 --> 00:09:45,202
<i>Within 2 minutes,
Adaline Bowman's core temperature</i>

74
00:09:45,394 --> 00:09:53,402
<i>had dropped to 87 degrees...
her heart stopped beating.</i>

75
00:10:00,100 --> 00:10:07,615
<i>At 8:55 a bolt of lightning struck
the vehicle discharging half a</i>

76
00:10:07,666 --> 00:10:12,908
<i>billion volts of electricity and
producing 60,000 amperes of current.</i>

77
00:10:12,958 --> 00:10:15,452
<i>Its effect was threefold.</i>

78
00:10:17,304 --> 00:10:21,229
<i>First, the charge defibrillated
Adaline Bowman's heart.</i>

79
00:10:23,433 --> 00:10:28,088
<i>Second,
she was jolted out of her anoxic state</i>

80
00:10:28,139 --> 00:10:33,086
<i>causing her to draw her
first breath in 2 minutes.</i>

81
00:10:46,966 --> 00:10:50,142
<i>Third, based on Von Lehman's principle of</i>

82
00:10:50,213 --> 00:10:53,967
<i>electron compression in
deoxyribonucleic acid,</i>

83
00:10:54,018 --> 00:10:57,692
<i>which will be discovered in the
year two thousand thirty-five,</i>

84
00:10:57,967 --> 00:11:03,711
<i>Adaline Bowman will henceforth be
immune to the ravages of time...</i>

85
00:11:03,763 --> 00:11:08,975
<i>she will never age another day.</i>

86
00:11:34,703 --> 00:11:37,847
<i>As the years passed,
Adaline credited her unchanging</i>

87
